flowRoot.flowPara: We don't care that much about how it's implemented, as long as it works.
Can have complex state that is difficult to implement in a lower level language. Less verifiable, but also more dynamic.
Needs to be fast light and small. Also verifiable and simple.
Many of these are DBus but others are less specified. They can be system specific.
This is the amount of code that actually interacts with the user and handles user input but also displaying information to the user.
These are the different components that gather information and bubbling it up to the level of the user. They can do this with the interfaces on the other side of the diagram.
